      "date": "2019-04-08 14:29:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nEmoly,\n\nI happened to see this.\n\nNormally, we backport  patches one bye one with full change log, it has some benifits\nfor example easier to track and confirm whether a specific bug have been fixed in the branch.\n\nFor example we confirmed an existed LU ticket which we could just use git log and then grep it to confirm patch have been merged.\n\nThe only benefit I could think of this is it only triggered build and test one time for several patches...",
